{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KUbT8JENeVuoC4DVfH1LHF","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the context I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report based on industry standards for OFX/QIF/CSV import and the schema you already have in place. Based on my analysis of your project structure and the existing schema design, here is my comprehensive analysis of the import pipeline for OFX/QIF/CSV:\n\n## Import Pipeline Architecture\n\nYour schema is already well-designed for imports with:\n- `import_batches` table to track import operations\n- `fitid` column in `transactions` for deduplication\n- Separate tracking via `import_batch_id`\n\n---\n\n## 1. OFX (Open Financial Exchange) Import\n\n### OFX Format Overview\nOFX is an SGML/XML-based format (SGML for versions < 2.0, XML for 2.0+). Banks typically provide OFX 1.x.\n\n### OFX File Structure\n```\nOFXHEADER:100\nSECURITY:NONE\nENCODING:USASCII\nCHARSET:1252\nCOMPRESSION:NONE\nOLDFILESPEC:102\nNEWFILESPEC:220\nSECURITY:NONE\n\n<OFX>\n<SIGNONMSGSRSV1>\n  <SONRS>\n    <STATUS>\n      <CODE>0\n      <SEVERITY>INFO\n    </STATUS>\n    <DTSERVER>20240315120000\n    <LANGUAGE>ENG\n  </SONRS>\n</SIGNONMSGSRSV1>\n\n<BANKMSGSRSV1>\n  <STMTTRNRS>\n    <STATUS>\n      <CODE>0\n      <SEVERITY>INFO\n    </STATUS>\n    <STMTRS>\n      <CURDEF>EUR\n      <BANKACCTFROM>\n        <BANKID>10001\n        <ACCTID>1234567890\n        <ACCTTYPE>CHECKING\n      </BANKACCTFROM>\n      <BANKTRANLIST>\n        <DTSTART>20240101\n        <DTEND>20240315\n        <STMTTRN>\n          <TRNTYPE>DEBIT\n          <DTPOSTED>20240315\n          <TRNAMT>-25.50\n          <FITID>2024031512345600001\n          <NAME>SUPERMARCHE XYZ\n          <MEMO>Courses alimentaires\n        </STMTTRN>\n        <STMTTRN>\n          <TRNTYPE>CREDIT\n          <DTPOSTED>20240301\n          <TRNAMT>1500.00\n          <FITID>2024030115000000001\n          <NAME>SALAIRE\n        </STMTTRN>\n      </BANKTRANLIST>\n      <LEDGERBAL>\n        <BALAMT>4567.89\n        <DTASOF>20240315\n      </LEDGERBAL>\n    </STMTRS>\n  </STMTTRNRS>\n</BANKMSGSRSV1>\n</OFX>\n```\n\n### OFX Key Fields Mapping\n```\nOFX Field          → Database Column\nFITID              → fitid (UNIQUE per account)\nDTPOSTED           → date\nTRNAMT             → amount\nNAME               → label\nMEMO               → note (optional)\nTRNTYPE            → (DEBIT/CREDIT determines sign)\nACCTID             → (maps to account_id)\n```\n\n### Deduplication Strategy (FITID)\n- **FITID** = Financial Institution Transaction ID\n- Unique identifier per transaction per account\n- Format: Often `YYYYMMDDHHMMSSNNNN` (timestamp + sequence)\n- **Dedup Logic**: \n  ```sql\n  INSERT OR IGNORE INTO transactions (..., fitid, ...)\n  WHERE NOT EXISTS (\n    SELECT 1 FROM transactions \n    WHERE account_id = ? AND fitid = ?\n  )\n  ```\n\n---\n\n## 2. QIF (Quicken Interchange Format) Import\n\n### QIF Format Overview\nPlain text, line-based format. Each transaction starts with `!Type` header.\n\n### QIF File Structure\n```\n!Account\nNMy Checking\nTBank\n^\n!Type:Bank\nD03/15/2024\nT-25.50\nPMarianne Dubois - Boulangerie\nL[Groceries]\n^\nD03/14/2024\nT-85.00\nPElectricité - EDF\nLUtilities\n^\n!Type:Bank\nD03/01/2024\nT1500.00\nPSALAIRE\nLIncome\n^\n```\n\n### QIF Key Fields Mapping\n```\nQIF Field   → Database Column\nD           → date (MM/DD/YYYY format)\nT           → amount (positive=debit, negative=credit typically)\nP           → label (payee)\nL           → series_id (category/label mapping)\nM           → note (memo)\nN           → not used (check number for bank transactions)\n!Account    → account metadata\n```\n\n### QIF Deduplication Strategy\n- **No native transaction ID** in QIF\n- Use composite key: `(account_id, date, amount, label)` hash\n- Or provide user with \"duplicate detection\" UI during import preview\n\n---\n\n## 3. CSV (Comma-Separated Values) Import\n\n### CSV Format Overview\nHighly variable depending on the bank. French banks commonly use:\n- **Encoding**: UTF-8 or ISO-8859-1\n- **Delimiter**: `;` (semicolon) or `,`\n- **Date Format**: `DD/MM/YYYY` or `YYYY-MM-DD`\n\n### Common French Bank CSV Structure\n```\nDate;Libellé;Montant;Solde\n01/03/2024;SUPERMARCHE XYZ;-25,50;4567,89\n15/02/2024;SALAIRE;1500,00;4593,39\n14/02/2024;EDF FACTURE;-85,00;3093,39\n```\n\n### Another Common Format (Crédit Agricole, BNP Paribas)\n```\nDate de l'opération;Date de valeur;Libellé;Débit;Crédit;Solde\n01/03/2024;01/03/2024;SUPERMARCHE XYZ;25,50;;4567,89\n15/02/2024;15/02/2024;SALAIRE;;1500,00;4593,39\n14/02/2024;14/02/2024;EDF FACTURE;85,00;;3093,39\n```\n\n### CSV Field Mapping (Flexible)\nUser configures mapping during import:\n```\nUser Input                  → Database Column\n\"Date\"                      → date\n\"Libellé\" or \"Description\" → label\n\"Montant\"                   → amount (handle sign detection)\n\"Memo\" or \"Details\"         → note\n\"Solde\"                     → (informational only, for balance check)\n```\n\n### CSV Deduplication Strategy\n- **No transaction ID** in CSV\n- Composite key: hash of `(date, amount, label)`\n- Detect duplicates by checking existing transactions\n- Show preview to user before import\n\n---\n\n## 4. Import Pipeline Logic (Rust Implementation)\n\n### Phase 1: File Reading & Format Detection\n```rust\npub enum ImportFormat {\n    OFX,\n    QIF,\n    CSV,\n}\n\npub fn detect_format(path: &Path) -> Result<ImportFormat> {\n    let content = std::fs::read_to_string(path)?;\n    \n    if content.contains(\"<OFX>\") || content.contains(\"OFXHEADER\") {\n        Ok(ImportFormat::OFX)\n    } else if content.contains(\"!Type:\") {\n        Ok(ImportFormat::QIF)\n    } else if content.contains(\";\") || content.contains(\",\") {\n        Ok(ImportFormat::CSV)\n    } else {\n        Err(\"Unknown format\")\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Phase 2: Parsing to Transactions\n```rust\npub struct RawTransaction {\n    pub date: String,\n    pub label: String,\n    pub amount: f64,\n    pub note: Option<String>,\n    pub fitid: Option<String>, // For OFX only\n}\n\npub fn parse_ofx(content: &str) -> Result<Vec<RawTransaction>> {\n    // Parse SGML/XML, extract STMTTRN blocks\n    // For each transaction:\n    // - Extract DTPOSTED, TRNAMT, NAME, MEMO, FITID\n    // - Convert DTPOSTED (YYYYMMDD) to date\n    // - Convert TRNAMT (with sign) to amount\n}\n\npub fn parse_qif(content: &str) -> Result<Vec<RawTransaction>> {\n    // Split by ^ delimiter\n    // For each block starting with D:\n    // - D = date (parse MM/DD/YYYY)\n    // - T = amount\n    // - P = label\n    // - M = note\n    // - L = category (store separately for mapping)\n}\n\npub fn parse_csv(content: &str, config: CsvConfig) -> Result<Vec<RawTransaction>> {\n    // Read header row, map to columns\n    // For each data row:\n    // - Extract date, label, amount based on column indices\n    // - Handle decimal separators (. vs ,)\n    // - Detect sign (if Debit/Credit columns, separate amounts)\n}\n```\n\n### Phase 3: Deduplication & Conflict Detection\n```rust\npub async fn check_duplicates(\n    db: &SqlitePool,\n    account_id: i64,\n    transactions: &[RawTransaction],\n) -> Result<DuplicateReport> {\n    let mut duplicates = Vec::new();\n    let mut conflicts = Vec::new();\n    \n    for tx in transactions {\n        // For OFX: check exact FITID match\n        if let Some(fitid) = &tx.fitid {\n            if db.query(\"SELECT id FROM transactions WHERE account_id = ? AND fitid = ?\")\n                .bind(account_id)\n                .bind(fitid)\n                .fetch_optional()\n                .await?\n                .is_some()\n            {\n                duplicates.push(tx.clone());\n            }\n        } else {\n            // For QIF/CSV: check composite key\n            let hash = hash_transaction(&tx);\n            if db.query(\"SELECT id FROM transactions WHERE account_id = ? AND hash = ?\")\n                .bind(account_id)\n                .bind(hash)\n                .fetch_optional()\n                .await?\n                .is_some()\n            {\n                duplicates.push(tx.clone());\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    \n    Ok(DuplicateReport { duplicates, conflicts })\n}\n```\n\n### Phase 4: Insertion with Batch Tracking\n```rust\npub async fn import_transactions(\n    db: &SqlitePool,\n    account_id: i64,\n    filename: &str,\n    format: ImportFormat,\n    transactions: Vec<RawTransaction>,\n) -> Result<ImportResult> {\n    // 1. Create import_batch record\n    let batch_id = db.execute(\n        \"INSERT INTO import_batches (filename, format, account_id, transaction_count)\n         VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?)\"\n    )\n    .bind(filename)\n    .bind(format.to_string())\n    .bind(account_id)\n    .bind(transactions.len())\n    .last_insert_rowid();\n    \n    // 2. Insert transactions within transaction block\n    let mut tx = db.begin().await?;\n    \n    for raw_tx in transactions {\n        let date = parse_date(&raw_tx.date)?;\n        let amount = normalize_amount(&raw_tx.amount);\n        \n        sqlx::query(\n            \"INSERT INTO transactions \n             (account_id, date, label, amount, note, fitid, import_batch_id)\n             VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)\"\n        )\n        .bind(account_id)\n        .bind(date)\n        .bind(&raw_tx.label)\n        .bind(amount)\n        .bind(&raw_tx.note)\n        .bind(&raw_tx.fitid)\n        .bind(batch_id)\n        .execute(&mut *tx)\n        .await?;\n    }\n    \n    tx.commit().await?;\n    \n    Ok(ImportResult {\n        batch_id,\n        imported_count: transactions.len(),\n        duplicates_skipped: 0,\n    })\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. Field Mappings Summary\n\n| OFX | QIF | CSV | Database |\n|-----|-----|-----|----------|\n| DTPOSTED | D | Date | `date` |\n| TRNAMT | T | Montant | `amount` |\n| NAME | P | Libellé | `label` |\n| MEMO | M | Memo | `note` |\n| FITID | (none) | (none) | `fitid` |\n| TRNTYPE | L | Catégorie | (mapped to `series_id`) |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Implementation Recommendations for Tauri/Rust\n\n1. **Use `ofxparse` or `nom` parser** for OFX (SGML is finicky)\n2. **Use `csv` crate** for CSV parsing with configurable delimiters\n3. **Use `chrono` crate** for date parsing (already in Cargo.toml)\n4. **Store raw FITID** in database for future re-imports (immutable dedup)\n5. **Implement import preview UI** showing:\n   - Detected duplicates\n   - Conflicts (date/amount mismatches)\n   - Unmatched categories\n   - Option to skip/merge/overwrite\n\n---\n\n## 7. Key Database Features Already in Schema\n\n✓ `import_batches` - Track import operations for rollback  \n✓ `fitid` column with index - Fast FITID dedup  \n✓ `import_batch_id` foreign key - Link transactions to imports  \n✓ `categorization_rules` - Auto-map labels to series  \n✓ `transaction_splits` - Split one transaction across multiple categories  \n\nYour schema is **production-ready** for these import formats!\n\n---\n\n## File Paths in Your Project\n\n```\n/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/src-tauri/src/\n  ├── main.rs                    (entry point)\n  ├── lib.rs                     (Tauri app setup)\n  ├── commands.rs                (IPC handlers) ← add import commands here\n  ├── db.rs                      (migrations)\n  └── import.rs                  (NEW: add this module)\n\n/home/jeremy/Documents/budgetview-tauri/src-tauri/migrations/\n  └── 001_initial_schema.sql     (already prepared with import_batches, fitid, etc.)\n```\n\nThis architecture gives you full offline-first import with proper deduplication and rollback capability!"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ab1cf9b7a34fd21ce (use SendMessage with to: 'ab1cf9b7a34fd21ce' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 40688\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 62686</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5670e2f2-2b23-453d-b13a-df268ffbafbe","uuid":"26288b17-496d-4b68-b06f-137e9ee4